---
import { RadioGroupDemo } from '../../components/form-control-demos';
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import { meta } from './_meta/radio-group';
---

<DocsLayout title={meta.label} description={meta.description}>
  <section class="gw-section">
    <div class="gw-width gw-stack--lg">
      <div class="gw-prose">
        <h1 class="gw-heading-l">RadioGroup</h1>
        <p>Use RadioGroup when users need to choose exactly one option from a short list.</p>
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">When to use</h2>
        <p>Use RadioGroup for prominent choices where seeing every option helps users answer quickly. The group renders a fieldset and legend so assistive technology announces the question before each option.</p>
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">When not to use</h2>
        <p>Do not use RadioGroup for long lists or searchable datasets. Use Select for compact single-choice lists, or design a dedicated autocomplete pattern for large datasets.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="gw-card gw-stack">
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Demo</h2>
        <RadioGroupDemo />
      </div>

      <div class="gw-card gw-stack">
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Accessibility notes</h2>
        <p class="gw-body--sm">RadioGroup requires a visible <code class="gw-mono">legend</code>. Hints and errors are connected to the fieldset with <code class="gw-mono">aria-describedby</code>.</p>
        <p class="gw-body--sm">Use short option labels. Add option hints only when a choice needs clarification.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
